WEBVTT

01:09.112 --> 01:11.462
[solemn music playing]

01:22.212 --> 01:23.866
[Padre Pio]
I know You shed tears.

01:24.910 --> 01:27.565
I know You continue
to shed tears every day

01:28.349 --> 01:30.176
because of man's ingratitude.

01:33.658 --> 01:35.051
You choose souls,

01:36.008 --> 01:38.489
and despite my unworthiness,
You've chosen me...

01:39.533 --> 01:40.578
to help You.

01:41.231 --> 01:43.146
And the more these souls suffer

01:43.277 --> 01:44.887
without the slightest
consolation,

01:45.017 --> 01:47.150
the more Your sufferings
are alleviated...

01:51.981 --> 01:54.070
in this consists all of my joy.

02:00.772 --> 02:02.513
I know You'll give me
what I need,

02:04.515 --> 02:06.169
I know You will not refuse it.

02:09.738 --> 02:11.131
I need courage.

02:12.915 --> 02:14.395
I know You will provide.

02:42.727 --> 02:43.728
[Padre Pio] Padre!

03:12.844 --> 03:13.889
I'm Pio.

03:27.859 --> 03:29.818
♪

03:42.787 --> 03:46.617
[church bells clanging]

04:06.811 --> 04:10.250
[indistinct chatter]

04:21.173 --> 04:24.264
[church bells
clanging continues]

04:54.511 --> 04:58.167
[indistinct chatter]

05:01.170 --> 05:02.214
Father.

05:12.877 --> 05:15.227
Franco, Franco, my husband?

05:15.358 --> 05:16.490
Giulio?

05:22.887 --> 05:25.368
Salvato? Giulio?

05:26.500 --> 05:27.501
I don't know.

05:29.067 --> 05:30.112
Oreste!

05:34.334 --> 05:36.118
I'm still a man.

05:36.248 --> 05:39.251
I'm still a man.
I'm back.

05:39.382 --> 05:41.471
Viva l'Italia,
viva l'Italia.

05:41.602 --> 05:43.908
[sobs]

05:44.039 --> 05:46.389
[Gerardo] Vincenzo, put him
in a chair, help him.

06:01.230 --> 06:02.623
- I'm back. I'm back.
- [Diana] Uncle.

06:02.753 --> 06:04.102
- Ciao,Elvira.
- [Diana] Uncle.

06:04.233 --> 06:08.106
Look at you! My baby!

06:08.237 --> 06:11.327
Look at you,
your uncle is back.

06:11.458 --> 06:13.198
Mom, mom. Mom.

06:14.983 --> 06:16.854
[Angelo] San Giovanni Rotondo
welcomes home

06:16.985 --> 06:19.074
his brave
and courageous soldiers.

06:19.204 --> 06:22.469
- [cheering]
- Viva l'Italia, viva l'Italia!

06:30.433 --> 06:31.434
My husband?

06:31.565 --> 06:33.088
[soldier]
I don't know, sorry.

06:41.618 --> 06:43.794
Anna. Anna.

06:45.492 --> 06:47.581
[sobbing]

06:50.845 --> 06:51.976
Look at you.

06:54.675 --> 06:57.982
Angelo, this is the list
of the dead.

07:12.170 --> 07:13.694
[Francesco]
Saponaro Nunzio?

07:23.051 --> 07:24.226
I cannot read.

07:31.363 --> 07:35.063
"I regret to inform you
that your son, Saponaro Nunzio,

07:35.193 --> 07:39.807
died from wounds
sustained on 26th October
while fighting on the Carso."

07:39.937 --> 07:43.463
[sobs, sniffles]

07:43.593 --> 07:46.117
[Francesco]
We have already lost
one son on the Carso.

07:54.343 --> 07:56.954
Your excellency, my husband?

07:57.085 --> 07:58.739
What is your husband's name?

07:58.869 --> 08:00.741
Giulio. Giulio Leogrande.

08:13.014 --> 08:16.365
Hopefully, he will be back
with the next group. Who knows?

08:17.932 --> 08:21.544
[sighs] Thank you.
Thank you. Thank you.

08:31.249 --> 08:33.904
[indistinct chatter]

08:41.956 --> 08:45.612
- [indistinct chatter]
- [laughter]

08:45.742 --> 08:47.701
[soldier]
Cheers, yeah, cheers.

08:47.831 --> 08:49.877
Look, instead of my eye.

08:51.313 --> 08:52.488
[soldier] We won!

08:53.707 --> 08:56.448
Wine, man, wine.
Viva l'Italia!

08:56.579 --> 08:58.755
- Viva l'Italia!
- Yeah!

08:58.886 --> 09:00.235
Yeah!

09:00.365 --> 09:01.889
Un brindisi.

09:02.019 --> 09:02.846
- Siì!
- Siì!

09:02.977 --> 09:04.500
[woman] Yeah!

09:04.631 --> 09:06.502
[laughter]

09:08.678 --> 09:12.203
[indistinct chatter]

09:12.334 --> 09:16.164
[praying in Latin]

09:27.479 --> 09:31.571
[praying in Latin]

09:47.282 --> 09:49.676
[Tonino] The sorrows
for Italy and for the world

09:49.806 --> 09:51.678
- is not finished.
- [utensils clatter]

09:51.808 --> 09:54.594
Every people
is still suffering of that

09:54.724 --> 10:00.338
and every families
are in grief or big sorrow.

10:00.469 --> 10:01.601
It's terrible.

10:03.864 --> 10:04.952
The king...

10:06.693 --> 10:07.694
Uh...

10:09.434 --> 10:13.134
Some intellectuals,
some interested in the...

10:14.265 --> 10:16.137
in the armies, militaries...

10:18.618 --> 10:19.575
Uh...

10:22.056 --> 10:27.496
Have convinced other people
to make war or compel them

10:31.369 --> 10:33.415
And the majority of Italians...

10:36.853 --> 10:39.160
do not want war.

10:41.771 --> 10:42.685
Christ...

10:44.731 --> 10:46.341
offered Himself,

10:48.517 --> 10:50.693
with His body,

10:50.824 --> 10:53.609
with His flesh to the Father,

10:55.524 --> 10:59.049
in similar way
we offer of our self,

11:00.311 --> 11:01.486
our bodies,

11:02.574 --> 11:03.750
our flesh

11:04.664 --> 11:05.708
to God

11:07.971 --> 11:09.973
in, uh, union with Christ.

11:11.714 --> 11:15.239
Sometimes this is suffering,
sometimes not,

11:15.370 --> 11:18.547
but the suffering
in union with Christ

11:18.678 --> 11:21.768
is a door to the Heaven.

11:23.770 --> 11:27.861
This em-- suffering lived alone

11:29.079 --> 11:30.515
is a door to Hell.

11:42.876 --> 11:44.921
[The Devil] So...

11:45.052 --> 11:47.489
you managed to avoid
going to war.

11:50.884 --> 11:52.712
You tried so hard

11:53.930 --> 11:55.932
and you finally succeeded.

12:03.070 --> 12:04.071
I'm ill.

12:08.510 --> 12:09.903
If I wasn't, I'd be there.

12:14.472 --> 12:18.389
You are no more than
a whimsical child
crying for his mother.

12:24.308 --> 12:25.745
My mother is the Madonna.

12:27.137 --> 12:28.182
Liar.

12:29.270 --> 12:32.229
The letters you wrote
to your devoted followers,

12:33.143 --> 12:35.624
that's what get you out
of your military service.

12:35.755 --> 12:36.712
No.

12:37.408 --> 12:39.193
Is that your little Madonna?

12:44.111 --> 12:47.592
Tell me, where you weeping
when you wrote this?

12:47.723 --> 12:49.769
Was your hand quivering?

12:52.467 --> 12:54.556
"I also must ask you a favor.

12:55.513 --> 12:59.996
I would very much like for you
to write to Donna Giovina Cevera

13:00.127 --> 13:02.956
in order for her
to put in a good word

13:03.086 --> 13:05.610
with these butcher superiors."

13:08.918 --> 13:10.050
"Butchers"?

13:16.360 --> 13:21.452
Those officers were doing
their duty. No more, no less.

13:23.411 --> 13:25.239
And to you they are butchers?

13:30.984 --> 13:32.376
I'm not scared of you.

13:38.078 --> 13:39.165
[exhales softly]

13:43.953 --> 13:45.868
I'm protected
by the blood of Christ.

13:47.522 --> 13:48.784
[exhales]

14:01.101 --> 14:03.538
- You're a coward.
- No.

14:03.668 --> 14:05.845
- You're a little boy.
- No.

14:05.975 --> 14:07.629
No courage.

14:07.759 --> 14:09.979
You ask others to have courage.

14:11.111 --> 14:12.634
A coward.

14:12.764 --> 14:15.506
- A piss-drenched coward.
- No.

14:18.901 --> 14:22.035
Let's talk about
a real coward.

14:24.080 --> 14:27.692
Let's talk about the trust,
the few that loved you,

14:27.823 --> 14:30.478
and the trust
you fucking abused,

14:30.608 --> 14:32.959
the fucking countless women
you fucking had,

14:33.089 --> 14:35.657
- your narcissistic...
- No... [sobs] No.

14:35.787 --> 14:37.311
- ...way with--
- No.

14:38.094 --> 14:39.617
- But here's where
it gets better.
- Shh!

14:39.748 --> 14:42.055
You stop now, you stop now.

14:42.185 --> 14:44.187
- In a few months--
- You say "Christ is Lord."

14:44.318 --> 14:45.972
You say "Christ is Lord."

14:46.102 --> 14:48.409
- In a few--
- You say "Christ is Lord!"

14:48.539 --> 14:51.238
Christ is Lord!
You say "Christ is Lord!"

14:51.368 --> 14:52.935
You say "Christ is Lord!"

14:53.066 --> 14:54.894
You say it! Say it!

14:55.024 --> 14:57.200
Say "Christ is Lord!"

14:57.331 --> 14:59.768
Christ is Lord!
You say "Christ is Lord!"

15:01.378 --> 15:03.903
[grunting]

15:06.079 --> 15:07.863
[Padre Pio groaning]

15:10.213 --> 15:13.825
[Padre Pio grunting, groaning]

15:19.353 --> 15:22.486
[groaning continues]

15:31.191 --> 15:33.715
- [breathing heavily]
- [growling]

15:35.847 --> 15:38.589
[groaning]

15:49.949 --> 15:51.733
[Padre Pio groaning, panting]

15:51.863 --> 15:55.171
- [objects clattering]
- [Padre Pio yelling]

16:03.005 --> 16:07.488
[Padre Pio groaning, panting]

16:09.925 --> 16:12.536
[breathing heavily]

16:18.455 --> 16:22.503
[labored breathing]

16:35.255 --> 16:38.519
[objects clattering]

16:48.007 --> 16:51.532
[Luigi] The primary source
of all human oppression
and exploitation

16:51.662 --> 16:53.664
is individual property.

16:53.795 --> 16:56.667
Oppression,
you know what it is?

16:56.798 --> 17:01.281
Oppression means cruel
and unjust treatment.

17:02.673 --> 17:04.066
It's what happened to you.

17:05.415 --> 17:08.375
You work hard
every day, right?

17:10.203 --> 17:11.726
You work all day or not?

17:12.857 --> 17:14.032
Do you ever stop?

17:16.252 --> 17:19.080
This is not right,
this is not fair.

17:19.212 --> 17:23.128
Exploitation means
that you're not the one

17:23.259 --> 17:25.653
who takes the benefit
from your work.

17:31.746 --> 17:34.705
"In nature, everything
is transformed.

17:34.836 --> 17:38.535
Nothing is created
and nothing is destroyed.

17:39.623 --> 17:41.277
Following this natural law

17:41.408 --> 17:42.844
that wants transformation

17:42.974 --> 17:46.065
is the struggle for existence
and the revolution."

17:49.242 --> 17:53.246
Nature is a cycle
of constant change.

17:53.376 --> 17:56.423
The way Spring arrives
after Winter,

17:56.553 --> 17:59.382
or the way... [chuckles]

17:59.513 --> 18:02.907
the calf grows
into the milk-giving cow.

18:04.474 --> 18:08.130
[mooing]

18:08.261 --> 18:09.697
[laughter]

18:11.481 --> 18:16.051
- [mooing]
- [laughter]

18:16.182 --> 18:19.228
[mooing]

18:20.969 --> 18:24.755
[laughter]

18:24.886 --> 18:26.105
You know that, right?

18:28.063 --> 18:29.369
That's what I'm saying.

18:32.067 --> 18:33.547
We need change.

18:36.811 --> 18:38.813
Change is a natural law.

18:40.945 --> 18:43.165
The land and everything
it gives us

18:43.296 --> 18:44.688
belongs to everybody.

18:44.819 --> 18:46.560
- [socialist] Yes.
- And one family can't control

18:46.690 --> 18:48.562
- San Giovanni Rotondo.
- [socialist] Yeah, that's true.

18:48.692 --> 18:50.129
Yeah, that's true.

18:51.130 --> 18:52.609
What is he talking about?

18:53.567 --> 18:57.527
He's talking about
how we can get control
of our lives.

18:58.398 --> 19:00.226
[Luigi]
I'm talking about freedom.

19:00.356 --> 19:04.360
To have freedom, we must stop
the exploitation by the masters.

19:04.491 --> 19:05.666
[Salvatore] Exploitation?

19:05.796 --> 19:07.755
You spent your life in school.

19:07.885 --> 19:09.931
- What are you saying?
- [scoffs]

19:10.061 --> 19:11.715
You are an Alberizzi,

19:11.846 --> 19:13.587
you're part
of a landowner family.

19:13.717 --> 19:15.676
- [Luigi] Calm.
- [socialist] That's true.

19:16.633 --> 19:20.942
How was life in Bologna
while we fought to protect you?

19:21.072 --> 19:22.683
Is this not a contradiction?

19:25.990 --> 19:27.949
You want to talk
about contradictions?

19:30.386 --> 19:31.474
You won right?

19:32.562 --> 19:33.911
But what did you win?

19:36.523 --> 19:40.744
This war led to nothing.
Our sacrifices led to nothing.

19:44.922 --> 19:46.097
Where's your husband?

19:49.884 --> 19:51.015
She doesn't know.

19:53.931 --> 19:55.063
Bring me a candle.

20:07.249 --> 20:08.946
[Luigi]
If a candle gives you light,

20:11.732 --> 20:13.951
do not curse the candle.

20:28.705 --> 20:32.231
[vehicle approaching]

20:48.508 --> 20:52.163
[indistinct chatter]

20:52.294 --> 20:53.295
[engine stops]

20:57.908 --> 21:00.868
[Angelo] Welcome, comrade.
Welcome back.

21:00.998 --> 21:02.173
[Silvestro]
How's everyone?

21:05.133 --> 21:06.090
Please.

21:34.467 --> 21:35.685
Please, have a seat.

21:37.339 --> 21:38.384
Have a seat.

21:55.009 --> 21:57.141
[Antonio]
I introduce you to Luigi.

21:57.272 --> 21:59.753
He's our young,
radical comrade.

22:01.450 --> 22:02.364
Pleasure.

22:03.452 --> 22:04.497
My pleasure.

22:09.545 --> 22:11.286
[Luigi] Now, in San Giovanni,

22:11.417 --> 22:13.332
they say that
I'm a revolutionary,

22:14.289 --> 22:18.249
a fire starter, it's true.

22:18.380 --> 22:20.382
But it's consciences
I want to set fire to.

22:20.513 --> 22:24.212
Yes, but let's focus
on winning the elections now.

22:24.343 --> 22:26.345
We need to speak
of winning votes.

22:27.258 --> 22:30.131
Do you think Lenin and Trotsky
cared about elections?

22:34.178 --> 22:37.268
[Silvestro]
Socialism is a process.

22:38.966 --> 22:41.403
So, comrades... [inhales]

22:41.534 --> 22:44.232
You must be careful
how you interpret

22:44.363 --> 22:47.409
the great Russian revolution.

22:47.540 --> 22:51.500
The world is not transformed

22:51.631 --> 22:56.070
by following the plans
that a prophet writes on paper

22:56.200 --> 22:58.289
or preaches to the masses.

23:01.684 --> 23:05.384
Their socialism is not ours.

23:07.690 --> 23:08.996
Social revolution...

23:10.650 --> 23:12.782
is not the creation

23:13.870 --> 23:15.829
of one man's will.

23:15.959 --> 23:19.876
Lenin is neither a leader
nor a prophet.

23:20.007 --> 23:21.400
He's a politician.

23:22.488 --> 23:26.405
So... [inhales] comrades,

23:26.535 --> 23:31.497
we will not take power
with violence,

23:31.627 --> 23:34.761
but with the consent
of the masses.

23:36.327 --> 23:41.115
We put our flag in good hands

23:41.245 --> 23:42.421
and we win.

23:49.645 --> 23:51.865
- Raised high...
- [chair squeaks]

23:51.995 --> 23:54.433
...for-- for all to see.

24:03.920 --> 24:08.272
- [smooch]
- [socialist] Yeah.

24:59.019 --> 25:00.020
[car door closes]

25:04.720 --> 25:05.808
What's going on?

25:07.723 --> 25:13.599
[praying in Latin]

25:13.729 --> 25:16.079
- [horse neighs]
- [praying in Latin]

25:22.390 --> 25:25.741
[tense music playing]

25:25.872 --> 25:27.917
[Silvestro groans, thuds]

25:28.048 --> 25:30.790
- [man grunts]
- [groaning continues]

25:41.409 --> 25:43.454
[groaning continues]

26:05.955 --> 26:08.088
♪

26:34.680 --> 26:35.681
Look at me.

26:37.857 --> 26:39.598
[breathing heavily]

26:39.728 --> 26:41.948
[Renato] We're not interested
in people like you in my town.

26:44.907 --> 26:46.039
Do you understand me?

26:48.215 --> 26:49.695
Now leave
and don't come back.

26:50.565 --> 26:51.697
Get him in the car.

26:53.829 --> 26:55.439
[Gerardo] Let's go
to the car, come on.

26:57.093 --> 26:58.138
[Silvestro groans]

27:02.055 --> 27:04.535
- [grunts]
- Get out of here, asshole.

27:04.666 --> 27:06.276
Get out of here, asshole.

27:07.538 --> 27:08.496
Go.

27:09.366 --> 27:12.021
- [Silvestro grunts]
- [engine starts]

27:16.286 --> 27:17.548
Don't come back.

27:22.162 --> 27:24.468
[birds chirping]

27:28.690 --> 27:32.172
[praying in Latin]

27:50.843 --> 27:53.410
[Latin prayer ends]

28:12.995 --> 28:15.128
[soft music playing]

28:27.053 --> 28:28.141
[smooches]

28:46.855 --> 28:50.467
[praying in Latin]

28:53.340 --> 28:57.866
[praying in Latin continues]

29:07.658 --> 29:09.617
[Padre Pio] My dearest
Father Benedetto...

29:10.749 --> 29:12.098
If I could fly,

29:13.055 --> 29:14.927
I'd like to shout.

29:15.057 --> 29:18.931
I'd like to cry out to everyone
at the top of my voice.

29:19.105 --> 29:20.802
Love Jesus.

29:21.890 --> 29:24.632
Love him who's
so deserving of love.

29:25.851 --> 29:27.243
But alas, my dear Father,

29:27.374 --> 29:30.203
my soul is still strongly
bound to the body

29:30.333 --> 29:33.684
and many are the sins which
impede the flight of my soul.

29:35.338 --> 29:37.384
If you could pray that
the Lord might be pleased

29:37.514 --> 29:38.907
to shorten my exile,

29:39.865 --> 29:42.519
and explain to me the origin
of this blind desire I have

29:42.650 --> 29:44.260
to depart from this life,

29:45.566 --> 29:46.741
I'd appreciate it.

29:47.742 --> 29:51.267
My sins are many
and they ought to check
my blind passion.

29:52.442 --> 29:55.184
I ponder over them, yet,

29:57.273 --> 29:59.710
I feel more and more attracted

29:59.841 --> 30:02.496
by the desire to take flight
from this world.

30:02.626 --> 30:04.672
[soft music playing]

30:04.803 --> 30:06.413
Do you recognize this?

30:07.849 --> 30:09.633
Is this the work of the ogre?

30:12.462 --> 30:14.682
Please keep me
continually warned.

30:18.425 --> 30:20.122
♪

31:43.858 --> 31:46.730
♪

32:04.574 --> 32:06.707
[fire crackling]

32:10.363 --> 32:12.539
[Antonio] These used to belong
to that poor little girl.

32:19.024 --> 32:20.895
Her mother asked me
to repair them.

32:23.028 --> 32:24.855
She won't be
needing them anymore.

32:26.683 --> 32:29.077
And what was her fault?
To be born poor?

32:33.560 --> 32:35.127
In the gospel it is written

32:35.257 --> 32:37.738
that it will be very difficult
for a rich man

32:37.868 --> 32:40.523
to enter the Kingdom of Heaven,

32:40.654 --> 32:44.353
while Marx said so too,
in his own way.

32:46.747 --> 32:49.141
[Angelo] You're talking about
the Kingdom of Heaven,

32:49.271 --> 32:51.012
but here we live in hell.

32:51.970 --> 32:53.623
I walk alone among them,

32:53.754 --> 32:55.625
in front of their ailments,

32:55.756 --> 32:57.932
their cries, their problems,

32:58.063 --> 32:59.499
most unsolvable.

32:59.629 --> 33:02.241
Here we need water,
we need a hospital.

33:02.371 --> 33:04.852
The little kid died because
I could not get the medicine

33:04.983 --> 33:06.549
I needed to save her.

33:07.637 --> 33:09.074
We need to change things.

33:09.204 --> 33:11.163
But we, the socialists,
are divided.

33:11.293 --> 33:13.208
We are against each other.

33:13.339 --> 33:14.949
[chuckles softly]

33:15.080 --> 33:17.560
Luigi wants to talk about
the brotherhood of the workers,

33:17.691 --> 33:20.955
but here we only have
the unemployed.

33:21.086 --> 33:24.176
And most of them
can neither read or write.

33:26.874 --> 33:28.093
I know it is hard.

33:30.878 --> 33:32.010
We are divided,

33:34.403 --> 33:36.231
but you do not despair,

33:37.580 --> 33:39.756
because whoever
is not with you

33:40.540 --> 33:42.455
is not necessarily
against you.

33:43.891 --> 33:45.240
Call them friends,

33:46.502 --> 33:48.330
if not brothers.

33:48.461 --> 33:51.768
And remember the words
of the poor carpenter

33:52.465 --> 33:56.599
when he said, "There is
no greater love than this,

33:56.730 --> 33:59.950
to give one's life
for one's friends."

34:00.908 --> 34:02.388
Friends, huh...

34:03.606 --> 34:07.132
Even shoes are divided
according to their social class.

34:07.262 --> 34:08.958
[sighs]

34:15.487 --> 34:20.058
[humming]

34:27.848 --> 34:29.241
[Padre Pio]
I feel that sometimes

34:29.371 --> 34:30.719
when I'm in the midst of prayer

34:30.893 --> 34:32.722
that I'm just...

34:32.853 --> 34:35.246
that I feel alone like I'm...

34:35.377 --> 34:37.771
I feel not alone like lonely,

34:37.900 --> 34:41.688
but alone like the Lord
has abandoned me,

34:41.818 --> 34:44.777
and I'm essentially
talking to myself.

34:48.042 --> 34:49.304
Do you feel in darkness?

34:49.435 --> 34:51.697
Yes, tremendous.

34:51.828 --> 34:52.916
Do you feel abandoned?

34:53.047 --> 34:54.004
Yes.

34:54.744 --> 34:58.618
And scared and baffled
and confused and...

34:58.748 --> 35:01.534
and like I'm sinning
but I don't--

35:01.664 --> 35:04.189
I don't know
if I'm sinning or not,

35:04.319 --> 35:06.365
because it feels like a sin
to the question these things,

35:06.495 --> 35:10.020
it feels like a sin
to be angry with the Lord.

35:10.151 --> 35:11.326
[sniffles]

35:11.457 --> 35:12.980
And I'm angry a lot.

35:13.111 --> 35:14.634
I feel angry a lot.

35:17.071 --> 35:19.769
- You know?
- I can tell you,

35:19.900 --> 35:21.467
the Lord hasn't
abandoned you.

35:22.424 --> 35:24.861
He's with you even
in the midst of darkness.

35:24.992 --> 35:25.993
[sniffles]

35:28.909 --> 35:30.432
You have to keep
your purer life,

35:30.563 --> 35:32.260
and receiving
the sacraments.

35:32.956 --> 35:34.610
It's the way,
it's the only way

35:34.741 --> 35:36.917
to be able to stay
in the right road.

35:37.047 --> 35:39.049
Without the Lord,
you can't do anything.

35:39.180 --> 35:40.181
I know.

35:43.402 --> 35:46.405
[praying in Latin]

35:58.460 --> 35:59.592
The war...

36:02.029 --> 36:04.510
took our two sons
away from us.

36:09.645 --> 36:11.169
They were both young.

36:13.606 --> 36:15.999
We cannot find a reason
to live anymore.

36:17.914 --> 36:19.916
But if God wanted this,

36:21.353 --> 36:22.484
even Him,

36:23.746 --> 36:25.487
why does He want
to keep us alive?

36:27.141 --> 36:28.621
- To torment us?
- No, no.

36:36.063 --> 36:38.196
War is a terrible thing,
Francesco.

36:40.546 --> 36:42.939
And your pain is real, yes.

36:44.680 --> 36:48.162
Do not let Satan take
advantage of your suffering.

36:49.468 --> 36:50.947
Do you understand?

36:51.078 --> 36:54.037
Blessed is the man who
endures the trial, Francesco.

36:57.519 --> 36:59.391
When I was young,

36:59.521 --> 37:01.958
my mother would do
embroidery at home,

37:02.089 --> 37:03.873
yes, sitting in a chair.

37:04.004 --> 37:07.616
And, uh, I, sitting in a stool,
looked up at the work...

37:10.880 --> 37:14.188
but I would only see it
from upside down.

37:14.319 --> 37:16.843
I'd see the knots
and the confused threads,

37:16.973 --> 37:18.758
and I'd say to my mother,
"What are you doing?

37:18.888 --> 37:20.063
What is this?

37:20.934 --> 37:22.152
Why is it so ugly?"

37:22.283 --> 37:24.590
And my mother,
she would lower the frame,

37:24.720 --> 37:27.157
and she would show me
the good side of the work,

37:27.288 --> 37:28.811
and I would see
all of the colors

37:28.942 --> 37:30.509
were in the right place

37:30.639 --> 37:32.250
and the pattern
was beautiful,

37:33.642 --> 37:34.817
precise.

37:42.303 --> 37:45.088
I, like you now,
can only see

37:45.219 --> 37:49.049
the work from upside down
'cause I was sitting
in a short stool, Francesco.

37:56.317 --> 37:58.667
If you lift your spirit
up in prayer,

38:01.279 --> 38:03.977
the Lord will show you
the design He has for you.

38:31.657 --> 38:32.571
Calm.

38:33.267 --> 38:34.355
Stay calm.

38:41.971 --> 38:43.364
[Gerardo]
What are you guys doing?

38:44.409 --> 38:46.585
We are we working the land
that you keep abandoned.

38:47.847 --> 38:49.239
They need it to eat.

38:49.370 --> 38:52.199
So if you're not using it,
we have the right to.

38:54.462 --> 38:55.463
[gun cocks]

39:01.469 --> 39:03.819
[Luigi] Socialism alone
will be enough

39:03.950 --> 39:05.647
to create the most
perfect balance

39:05.778 --> 39:07.867
between men, order,
and peace,

39:07.997 --> 39:10.260
because human beings,
in their free development,

39:10.391 --> 39:13.263
will understand that no man
can be truly free and happy

39:13.394 --> 39:16.223
- if not in the respect
of all humanity.
- What are you guys looking at?

39:16.354 --> 39:19.095
Huh? Leave my land now!

39:19.226 --> 39:20.836
- [gunshots]
- [horse neighs]

39:20.967 --> 39:21.968
[Gerardo] Get out of here!

39:23.839 --> 39:25.624
Leave now!

39:27.408 --> 39:29.236
I'm gonna kill you all!

39:29.367 --> 39:31.630
- [gunshots]
- [Gerardo] Do you hear me? All!

39:31.760 --> 39:33.240
- Get out of here!
- [gunshot continues]

39:33.371 --> 39:34.502
[man] Luigi, run!

39:34.633 --> 39:36.286
- [woman] Run! Run!
- [Gerardo] Go!

39:36.983 --> 39:40.943
Okay? All of you, guys,
this is my land!

39:42.162 --> 39:45.861
Hey, Luigi, if you ever
come back here, I shoot you!

39:46.775 --> 39:49.125
[praying in Latin]

40:03.966 --> 40:07.709
[praying in Latin]

40:25.597 --> 40:29.470
[praying in Latin]

40:36.346 --> 40:40.220
[praying in Latin]

40:50.883 --> 40:54.452
[praying in Latin]

42:16.316 --> 42:17.622
[grunting softly]

42:50.306 --> 42:51.351
Listen.

43:02.536 --> 43:05.495
[breathing heavily]

43:12.590 --> 43:14.548
Have the courage
to do what you hear.

43:30.477 --> 43:32.348
[praying in Latin]

43:45.971 --> 43:47.407
[sniffles]

44:02.422 --> 44:03.553
[grunts softly]

44:46.161 --> 44:48.468
[rocks thudding]

44:53.038 --> 44:54.779
Come on, come on.

45:12.927 --> 45:14.189
[Vincenzo] Work, work.

45:22.545 --> 45:23.938
How about your man?

45:26.636 --> 45:27.899
Any news from him?

45:33.295 --> 45:35.123
Go and talk
with some other woman,

45:35.254 --> 45:36.603
I have a husband.

45:41.608 --> 45:44.872
[Salvatore groaning, coughing]

45:45.003 --> 45:47.048
I go! I go!

45:49.224 --> 45:50.399
I go!

45:55.100 --> 45:58.712
[coughing] I go! I go!

46:04.109 --> 46:06.546
♪

46:19.167 --> 46:20.516
[coughing]

46:54.899 --> 46:57.510
[Michele]
Salvatore! Salvatore!

46:57.640 --> 46:59.207
- Salvatore!
- [woman] Salvatore!

47:00.818 --> 47:01.906
Salvatore!

47:02.036 --> 47:03.081
Fast, fast!

47:05.126 --> 47:07.737
- What happened? Salvatore!
- [coughing]

47:07.868 --> 47:08.869
[woman] Salvato!

47:13.482 --> 47:15.745
[indistinct]

47:24.363 --> 47:25.799
[Michele] A doctor!

47:50.389 --> 47:53.914
♪

48:26.294 --> 48:27.556
[Salvatore breathing heavily]

49:01.939 --> 49:03.984
What are you doing?
Go back to work, come on.

49:07.553 --> 49:09.294
Vincenzo, don't let anyone in.

49:12.558 --> 49:13.863
Doctor's coming, get out.

49:16.170 --> 49:17.084
Out!

50:04.392 --> 50:06.220
Poor man, he made it
through the war.

50:10.877 --> 50:12.139
Tell them he's still alive.

50:13.010 --> 50:14.315
[Angelo] What?

50:14.446 --> 50:16.926
You go out, you tell them
he's still alive,

50:17.057 --> 50:18.841
or else things
are gonna get ugly here.

50:20.626 --> 50:23.411
I'll have no part in this.
This man is dead!

50:23.542 --> 50:25.805
I don't care, you tell them
he's still alive,

50:25.935 --> 50:28.503
that we need to take him
to the hospital, okay?

50:29.722 --> 50:30.940
I will not.

50:33.160 --> 50:34.292
- No?
- No.

50:35.249 --> 50:37.251
So if anybody gets hurt
it's on you, okay?

50:40.428 --> 50:42.952
Everything is going
to be alright, okay?

50:43.083 --> 50:44.563
Now go back to work.

50:52.049 --> 50:53.398
I'm not going anywhere.

50:54.399 --> 50:55.487
I will wait here.

50:58.968 --> 51:02.102
What are you saying?
Go to work or you go back home.

51:02.972 --> 51:04.235
Come on, go to work.

51:06.106 --> 51:08.587
Look how good you are
serving your boss.

51:08.717 --> 51:11.068
It's the slave labor
that made him sick.

51:15.246 --> 51:16.160
Go.

51:24.255 --> 51:26.648
It's the slave labor
that made him sick.

51:30.087 --> 51:31.305
What are you doing?

51:31.436 --> 51:33.351
Go back to work
or I'll send you off,

51:33.481 --> 51:34.787
and I'm not paying you.

51:34.917 --> 51:36.919
Go back to work. Go!

51:38.095 --> 51:39.096
Come on!

51:49.889 --> 51:52.413
- I'm going home. Fuck your pay.
- [Renato] Yeah, go home.

52:00.291 --> 52:02.728
[Padre Pio]
...the Lord is with thee.

52:02.858 --> 52:05.339
Blessed art thou among women

52:06.384 --> 52:09.561
and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus.

52:10.562 --> 52:12.999
Holy Mary, Mother of God,

52:13.130 --> 52:15.088
pray for us sinners,

52:15.219 --> 52:17.046
now and at the hour
of our death.

52:17.177 --> 52:18.222
Amen.

52:19.484 --> 52:24.010
Hail Mary, full of grace,
the Lord is with thee.

52:24.141 --> 52:26.665
Blessed art thou among women

52:26.795 --> 52:29.363
and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus.

52:30.886 --> 52:33.585
- Holy Mary, Mother of God...
- [Anna crying]

52:33.715 --> 52:36.109
...pray for us sinners,

52:36.240 --> 52:37.980
now and at the hour
of our death.

52:40.200 --> 52:41.419
[sobbing]

52:41.549 --> 52:43.551
[Padre Pio] ...full of grace,

52:43.682 --> 52:45.118
the Lord is with thee.

52:45.858 --> 52:48.034
Blessed art thou among women

52:48.165 --> 52:50.602
and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus.

52:51.603 --> 52:53.518
Holy Mary, Mother of God,

52:53.648 --> 52:56.129
pray for us sinners,

52:56.260 --> 52:58.697
now and at the hour
of our death. Amen.

53:00.002 --> 53:01.743
[crying continues]

53:44.264 --> 53:47.572
[crying continues]

54:45.717 --> 54:47.196
[crying]

55:03.996 --> 55:05.171
[sniffles]

55:10.959 --> 55:13.484
[Angelo] That's the effect
of the poison gas from the war.

55:17.270 --> 55:18.532
He never should
have been working.

55:18.663 --> 55:20.708
What was he going
to do? Starve?

55:21.970 --> 55:24.408
So let's not let him
die in vain. Hm?

55:33.808 --> 55:35.767
Hi, Francesco.

55:35.897 --> 55:37.159
- Hi.
- How are you?

55:37.290 --> 55:39.292
- Mm.
- You gotta be strong, eh?

55:39.423 --> 55:40.772
- Thank you.
- You have to be strong.

55:40.902 --> 55:42.513
Listen. Have you registered?

55:42.643 --> 55:43.949
N-no, not yet.

55:44.079 --> 55:46.734
You need to vote, brother.
You need to vote.

55:46.865 --> 55:49.607
It's our opportunity here.
We have to stick together.

55:49.737 --> 55:51.652
- Hm?
- I will.

55:53.350 --> 55:54.481
You already registered right?

55:54.612 --> 55:56.135
Yeah, we already done, brother.

55:56.265 --> 55:57.528
That's not the point.

55:57.658 --> 55:59.181
[Luigi] You still talking
about elections?

55:59.312 --> 56:01.314
- Yeah. What do you think?
- [Antonio] It is important.

56:02.576 --> 56:04.491
It's our opportunity
to act together.

56:05.318 --> 56:07.973
It's time we start doing to them
what they have been doing to us.

56:10.062 --> 56:11.629
[Michele] The two of you
can't come in here.

56:12.804 --> 56:13.979
[Vincenzo] Who says so?

56:16.503 --> 56:18.984
[Michele] We do.
The socialists.

56:20.289 --> 56:22.335
We're all from the same village.

56:22.466 --> 56:24.337
[Michele] Tell your friend
to be ashamed.

56:24.468 --> 56:27.035
Tell him he's so friendly
with his masters

56:27.166 --> 56:29.386
that now he has become
their lap dog.

56:31.083 --> 56:32.650
- [grunting]
- [indistinct shouting]

56:32.780 --> 56:35.435
[Angelo]
That's enough now! Hey!

56:35.566 --> 56:37.263
Pay some respect
for the dead!

56:37.394 --> 56:39.483
[Luigi] They have no respect
for the living.

56:40.397 --> 56:43.051
And you have no respect
for those who fought
for their country.

56:43.182 --> 56:44.966
[spits]

56:45.097 --> 56:46.794
You mean for your masters,
right?

56:47.708 --> 56:49.231
Some raw deal you got.

56:49.362 --> 56:51.886
[socialists jeering]

56:53.845 --> 56:55.629
You're gonna pay for that.

56:59.111 --> 57:00.547
I'll be waiting for you.

57:12.777 --> 57:14.866
♪

57:20.785 --> 57:21.916
[imitates gunshot]

57:23.396 --> 57:26.051
Don Anselmo,
I wanna show you a thing.

57:26.181 --> 57:28.096
You know, this is custom-made
by my family.

57:28.227 --> 57:31.230
My grandfather gave it to me,
I'm gonna give it to my son.

57:31.360 --> 57:32.710
It's a family tradition,
you know?

57:32.840 --> 57:35.713
Hold it, it's a beautiful gun,
beautiful.

57:36.844 --> 57:39.194
[chuckles]

57:39.325 --> 57:40.892
[Renato] I know
you like hunting.

57:41.022 --> 57:42.807
Why don't you come hunt
with us one day?

57:44.156 --> 57:45.374
[Don Anselmo scoffs]

57:48.029 --> 57:49.901
- Thank you very much.
- You're welcome.

57:51.206 --> 57:52.773
- For you, Father.
- Here.

57:52.904 --> 57:54.732
- Thank you.
- Give it to me.

57:54.862 --> 57:56.037
[sighs]

58:03.175 --> 58:04.698
- [Renato] Elvira.
- Yeah?

58:04.829 --> 58:06.570
- Give him the money.
- Oh, okay.

58:10.574 --> 58:12.227
Father,

58:13.925 --> 58:16.580
we want to give you a little
something for the parish.

58:22.063 --> 58:24.501
- Next to my heart.
- [Elvira chuckles]

58:24.631 --> 58:29.288
♪

58:38.210 --> 58:39.428
[engine stops]

58:41.300 --> 58:43.302
- Bruno.
- Gerardo.

58:43.432 --> 58:44.869
[Gerardo] Let's go upstairs.

58:59.927 --> 59:02.147
He's a friend of mine,
Bruno Bevere.

59:02.277 --> 59:03.540
My mom, my aunt.

59:03.670 --> 59:04.715
- Elvira is, uh...
- Hi.

59:04.845 --> 59:06.151
She's Renato's wife.

59:07.152 --> 59:08.457
- Uh...
- Good.

59:12.157 --> 59:13.375
A friend is here.

59:15.769 --> 59:19.251
- Good evening, Renato.
- Bruno.

59:19.381 --> 59:21.253
- [glass clinking]
- Father.

59:25.910 --> 59:27.564
Join us, take a seat, Bruno.

59:27.694 --> 59:28.826
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

59:29.870 --> 59:31.437
May I offer you
something to drink?

59:32.351 --> 59:33.482
Mm-hmm.

59:39.227 --> 59:41.273
[Renato] So, I was talking
with Don Anselmo.

59:41.403 --> 59:44.929
We were making final plans
about the election. [sighs]

59:45.059 --> 59:47.714
I'm sure I will win. I mean,
I have no doubt about it.

59:48.846 --> 59:50.891
But you know,
if the other side just...

59:52.153 --> 59:54.155
If they create a riot,
or if they--

59:54.286 --> 59:56.897
if they, like, manipulate
the actual voting,

59:57.028 --> 59:58.595
that--that could be
a problem.

01:00:00.727 --> 01:00:02.381
That's why I am here.

01:00:04.296 --> 01:00:05.645
[Gerardo inhales]

01:00:05.776 --> 01:00:09.431
I've been away
at the front for so long.

01:00:10.215 --> 01:00:13.044
You know,
I fought for two years

01:00:13.174 --> 01:00:15.568
and then I come back here,
you know,

01:00:15.699 --> 01:00:18.049
and I have to worry
about all this.

01:00:19.616 --> 01:00:21.182
The election.

01:00:22.357 --> 01:00:25.230
I mean, this is insane.

01:00:25.360 --> 01:00:27.667
These people,
they've been working for us

01:00:27.798 --> 01:00:29.495
forever, you know,

01:00:29.626 --> 01:00:32.324
and now you're
expecting them to vote.

01:00:32.454 --> 01:00:35.022
I just-- you know,
I don't get it.

01:00:35.153 --> 01:00:36.720
They have no rights.

01:00:36.850 --> 01:00:40.201
I mean, these people
are, you know,

01:00:40.332 --> 01:00:42.377
- nothing.
- It's the first free election

01:00:42.508 --> 01:00:43.944
we have in our country.

01:00:44.075 --> 01:00:45.903
- Hmm.
- You fought for it.

01:00:47.034 --> 01:00:48.122
Appreciate it.

01:00:49.907 --> 01:00:53.867
♪

01:01:06.706 --> 01:01:08.447
- [Vincenzo] Hey.
- Who's there?

01:01:11.145 --> 01:01:12.364
[Renato] What's happening?

01:01:17.761 --> 01:01:19.066
Come in here, come.

01:01:27.684 --> 01:01:29.947
[Vincenzo] Michele,
I want to kill him!

01:01:30.077 --> 01:01:31.470
[Renato] What's happening?

01:01:31.600 --> 01:01:33.515
I should have killed them all.

01:01:36.693 --> 01:01:39.086
Luigi Fiore said
he will kill all of us.

01:01:40.174 --> 01:01:41.828
[Gerardo] Our cousin, Luigi.

01:01:42.829 --> 01:01:45.092
We send this little punk
to university

01:01:45.223 --> 01:01:47.704
and he comes back
with those ideas, huh?

01:01:47.834 --> 01:01:51.446
Didn't they teach him
this is Italy, not Russia?

01:01:51.577 --> 01:01:53.971
Luigi Fiore and who else?

01:01:57.409 --> 01:01:58.497
Who else?

01:01:59.541 --> 01:02:00.586
[Vincenzo] And, uh...

01:02:03.545 --> 01:02:04.677
Michele Russo.

01:02:10.030 --> 01:02:12.685
Angelo Rinaldi, the doctor,

01:02:13.512 --> 01:02:16.428
he cannot control them,
he's too weak.

01:02:18.038 --> 01:02:22.042
Two decorated for valor,
you and you.

01:02:22.173 --> 01:02:24.349
One wounded in war.

01:02:24.479 --> 01:02:26.394
And now you,

01:02:26.525 --> 01:02:29.833
the respectable people
of this village

01:02:29.963 --> 01:02:33.358
must be subjected to this.

01:02:33.488 --> 01:02:37.536
These socialists need a lesson

01:02:37.666 --> 01:02:41.583
about life and death,

01:02:41.714 --> 01:02:45.022
but they don't believe, so...

01:02:46.153 --> 01:02:47.894
they won't need a priest.

01:02:48.634 --> 01:02:51.289
Otherwise,

01:02:51.419 --> 01:02:56.294
they will end up preventing you
from baptizing your children,

01:02:58.078 --> 01:02:59.776
abusing your women.

01:03:01.995 --> 01:03:03.910
They will kill the priests,

01:03:05.433 --> 01:03:08.306
and use churches for barns.

01:03:23.669 --> 01:03:25.932
[Renato's aunt]
There's someone out there!

01:03:26.063 --> 01:03:27.629
[Renato] Get down,
get down. Move, move!

01:03:27.760 --> 01:03:28.805
[Elvira] Diana.

01:03:30.458 --> 01:03:32.591
- [chairs squeaking]
- [Gerardo] Get down, get down.

01:03:32.721 --> 01:03:34.201
Stay back, stay back.

01:03:36.769 --> 01:03:37.988
The weapons.

01:04:12.022 --> 01:04:14.851
[church bells clanging]

01:05:14.823 --> 01:05:18.349
[praying in Latin]

01:05:24.181 --> 01:05:26.096
